>such as Sustrans</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">’ ‘Better by Design’ training</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> – </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">to</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> support local authorities and the </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Highways Agency</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  The objective must be</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> to place the needs of cyclists alongside those of motorists. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="8" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.1pt; padding-left:14.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Design standards and guidance for planners and </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">designers of roads, such as LTN 2/08</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">TfL’s ‘London Cycle Design Standards’, are available and if used properly should lead to good design.  The challenge for cycle proofing roads is getting planners and engineers to routinely implement </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">the</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">se standards,</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">when provision for cycling </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">has traditionally been</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> an afterthough</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">t </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">in</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> highway works. Government </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">should expressly require provision for cycling to be a primary consideration </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">in bids for transport</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> funding.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.35pt; text-indent:-28.35pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 14.1pt; padding-left:14.25pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Regulations, in particular those related to signs</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> make innovation a slow and difficult process when a local authority wishes to depart from the current </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">‘Traffic Signs Regulations and General Directions 2002’</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (TSRGD)</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">While the recent signing review has enabled some modest changes, the fact that it will t</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ake in excess of five years and primary legislation to achieve some changes is a barrier</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> that has to be removed.  </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Reduce default speed limits on </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">urban and </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">local rural roads</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 20.55pt; padding-left:7.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">percentage</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">of pedestrians</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> or cyclists</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> killed when hit by a car reduces as vehicle speed is reduced. One</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">study found that at 20mph there was a 2.5% chance of being fatally injured, compared to a</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">20% chance at </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">30mph</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">. In </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Portsmouth</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">, the introduction of signs only</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">20mph</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">limits led to a 22% reduct</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">ion in casualties, compared to a national reduction of 14% in </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">comparable areas. </span></li><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 20.55pt; padding-left:7.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">The </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">British Medical Journal</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> published comprehensive research into </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">local </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">20 mph zones in </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">London</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> in 2009, which showed a reduction in casualties and collision</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> of around 40%, </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">reduction in children killed or</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> seriously injured of 50% and reduction in casualties among cyclists by 17%.</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> While m</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">odelling work by the North West Public Health Observatory showed that the adoption of 20mph limits across the region would result in 400 fewe</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">r child deaths or serious injuries.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 20.55pt; padding-left:7.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Reducing traffic speeds has been clearly demonstrated to encourage people to cycle</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">more for local trips. In </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Bristol</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">, the results of a pilot</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> programme of 20mph speed limits</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> found that walking and cycling had increased by 12% within the </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">areas </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">(Bristol City Council, 2011).</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Tackle dangers posed by HGV’s</span></p><ol start="13" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 20.55pt; padding-left:7.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">In </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">London</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">, HGV</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">’</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">s were involved in 53% of cycling fatalities in 2011 despite making up just 4% of the traffic. A study by Transport for </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">London</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (TfL) showed that cyclists involved in collisions with </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">HGV’s</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> are 78 times more likely to be killed than those hit by a car.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 20.55pt; padding-left:7.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Most </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">cyclist and Heavy Goods Vehicle (HGV) collisions happen when vehicles turn left at traffic lights or other junctions. Additionally, research from Transport for </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">London</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> (TfL) shows that vehicles without sideguards are involved in a disproportionate number of</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> fatal collisions with cyclists.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:normal; margin:6pt 0pt 6pt 20.55pt; padding-left:7.8pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Sustrans welcomes action from DfT and Transport for London (TfL) to establish </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">a </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">new industrial HGV task force to take action against dangerous HGV drivers, vehicles and operators.</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> However, in addition to schemes such as TfL</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">’s Safer Lorry Charge. Governments should look to learn from other cities such as </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">Paris</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">where</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> larger vehicles</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> may</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> only deliver </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">between</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> 10pm </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">and </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">7am – significantly reducing the </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">exposure of cyclists to the risk of collision with HGV’s</span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">November 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="color:#808080; font-family:'Helvetica 55 Roman'; font-size:8pt">3</span></p></div></body></html>